A sea captain is always the âold man,â be his age what it may. Captain
Le Fargesâ age might have been forty-five. He was a sailor of the Jean
Bart type, of French descent, but a naturalised American.

âI donât know where the windâs gone,â said the captain as he drew near
the man in the deck chair. âI guess itâs blown a hole in the firmament,
