was not sure.â

âNo,â replied Stannistreet, âhe only spoke of the beach.â

âYes. Well, suppose there were natives at the other side of the island
who had taken these children.â

âIf so, they would grow up with the natives.â

âAnd become savages?â

âYes; but the Polynesians canât be really called savages; they are a
very decent lot. Iâve knocked about amongst them a good while, and a
kanaka is as white as a white manâwhich is not saying much, but itâs
